# LLM Wiki (Karpathy pattern)

Workspace wiki root: [`wiki/`](../../wiki/). **You own the wiki layer** (markdown under `wiki/` except `wiki/raw/`). The user curates direction; you do filing, cross-links, and bookkeeping.

## When to update (no reminder needed)

Do **not** wait for “put this in the wiki.” After **substantive** work (research, debugging, design, ops), if **any** of this became true, integrate before you stop:

- Non-obvious fact, constraint, or command that will matter in a **later** session.
- A mistake, false assumption, or fix worth **not repeating**.
- A stable decision or rationale **not** captured in an ADR, plan file, or scoped pipeline artifact.
- A good synthesis, comparison, or answer the user might ask again — **file it**, not only chat.

Skip trivia, secrets, one-off typos, or anything already the single source of truth in `pipelines/` scoped output or upstream submodule docs (link instead).

## What to touch each time

1. **Create or edit** the relevant topic/entity pages under `wiki/` (relative links between pages).
2. Update [`wiki/index.md`](../../wiki/index.md): entry or one-line summary per page; keep categories honest.
3. Append one line to [`wiki/log.md`](../../wiki/log.md): `## [YYYY-MM-DD] ingest \| Short title` or `query \|`, `lint \|`, `update \|` as appropriate.

Optional **raw** inputs for later ingest live only under [`wiki/raw/`](../../wiki/raw/) (immutable for agents — summarize into wiki pages, do not edit sources).

## Query habit

When the user asks something that may already be compiled, **read `wiki/index.md` first**, then open linked pages. Prefer citing/updating the wiki over rediscovering from scratch.

## Lint

If the user asks to clean up the wiki, invokes **`@wiki-lint`**, or pages grow stale, run a **lint pass** per [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) (Trigger `@wiki-lint`): contradictions, orphans, missing links, stale claims; fix in place and log it.
